cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new technique for accelerating training in supervised learning. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as importance sampling is a common technique in AI research. Additionally, the paper uses synthetic problems and popular datasets, which suggests it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper's focus on reducing stochastic variance and improving training time suggests it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
